HEADWORD: Proudly
<hw>Proud"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a proud manner; with lofty
airs or mien; haughtily; arrogantly; boastfully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Proudly</qex> he marches on, and void of fear.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proudness</ent>⟦br⟧
